Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["EnsembleAverage", "Subsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5067588809059*^9, 3.506758883800753*^9}, {
   3.506794559463007*^9, 3.506794559870281*^9}, 
   3.506855386938195*^9},ExpressionUUID->"1ccb2c0d-26f9-486b-b839-\
27f0db0745d0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"EnsembleAverage", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<EnsembleAverage is an option for high-level SpinDynamica routines \
including Signal1D, Trajectory, TransformationAmplitude and \
TransformationAmplitudeTable. The default is EnsembleAverage\[Rule]False, in \
which case no ensemble averaging is done. A general specification is \
EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{var,samplingscheme}, which implements an ensemble \
average of the variable var, using the scheme samplingscheme, which takes the \
form {{{val1},weight1},{{val2},weight2}...}. The computation is performed for \
all the defined values {val1,val2..} of the variable var, and the results \
superposed using the weights {weight1,weight2..}. Simplified syntax of the \
form EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{var,{val1,val2..}} assumes equally weighted \
values (summing to 1).\nThe sampling scheme may also be implemented over \
multiple variables. For example, the syntax EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{{\[Alpha],\
\[Beta],\[Gamma]},{{{\[Alpha]1,\[Beta]1,\[Gamma]1},w1}, {{\[Alpha]2,\[Beta]2,\
\[Gamma]2},w2}..} implements summation over a set of Euler angles {\[Alpha],\
\[Beta],\[Gamma]} with the specified values and weights. \nEach of the \
EnsembleAverage variables may also be multidimensional, i.e. having a value \
which is a list. For example, the syntax EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{\
\[CapitalOmega],{{{\[Alpha]1,\[Beta]1,\[Gamma]1},w1}, {{\[Alpha]2,\[Beta]2,\
\[Gamma]2},w2}..} implements a summation over a variable \[CapitalOmega], \
which takes values given by the three-element lists of Euler angle triplets \
{{\[Alpha]1,\[Beta]1,\[Gamma]1}, {\[Alpha]2,\[Beta]2,\[Gamma]2},..} etc. with \
computations summed using the weights {w1, w2...}. \nPredefined Euler angle \
sets for powder averaging are available through syntax of the form \
EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{\[CapitalOmega],OrientationsAndWeights[<scheme>]} or \
EnsembleAverage\[Rule]{{\[Alpha],\[Beta],\[Gamma]},OrientationsAndWeights[<\
scheme>]}. Execute ?OrientationsAndWeights for more information. \nThe \
ensemble variables may appear in any of the other arguments of the high-level \
SpinDynamica routine, including option specifications such as \
BackgroundGenerator. \nThe additional option setting Parallel\[Rule]True \
distributes computation of the EnsembleAverage over the available kernels.\n\
\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 PageWidth:>WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.469878218285511*^9, 3.469878219035956*^9}, {
   3.469882329319214*^9, 3.46988233483611*^9}, {3.4698823788891363`*^9, 
